Global Gelfoam Market Insights
Gelfoam Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Gelfoam Market Overview
The global Gelfoam market size was valued at approximately USD 1.2 billion in 2023 and is expected to grow at a CAGR of around 6.1% from 2024 to 2030. Gelfoam is primarily used in medical applications, such as in surgery, for controlling bleeding and promoting clotting. The market is driven by the increasing demand for surgical procedures, advancements in wound care, and rising awareness regarding safe surgical practices. Additionally, the growing elderly population and the expansion of healthcare facilities globally are boosting market growth. However, the high cost of production and stringent regulations related to medical device approvals are some of the key challenges affecting the market growth.

